Usage: ecoSplitComplexFlop [-help] [-force] [-legal] [-power] [-skipRoute] {-inst <flopInstName> | -listFile <instNamesFile> | -all } [-preCTS  | -postCTS  | -postRoute ]

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-all                          # Process all flop instances in design. Default
                              # is false. (bool, optional)
-force                        # Force to decompose flop regardless timing
                              # gains. Default is false. (bool, optional)
-inst <flopInstName>          # The names of the flop instance to be
                              # decomposed. (string, required)
-legal                        # To place the decomposed flop and combinational
                              # cells at legal location. Default is false.
                              # (bool, optional)
-listFile <instNamesFile>     # The file containing names of flop instances to
                              # be decomposed. Specify one instance per line.
                              # Comment with #. Instance name can not contain
                              # spaces or backslashes. (string, required)
-postCTS                      # Set -postCTS if design state is postCTS.
                              # (bool, optional)
-postRoute                    # Set -postRoute if design state is postRoute.
                              # (bool, optional)
-power                        # Decompose complex flop to reclaim power.
                              # Default is false. (bool, optional)
-preCTS                       # Set -preCTS if design state is preCTS.
                              # (bool, optional)
-skipRoute                    # Skip globalDetailRoute after decomposition in
                              # postRoute stage. (bool, optional)